article.description: Peters leads Valparaiso in 93-58 rout of Murray St
article.headline: Peters leads Valparaiso in 93-58 rout of Murray St
article.linkText: Peters leads Valparaiso in 93-58 rout of Murray St
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Alec Peters scored 26 points and Darien Walker chipped in 18 as Valparaiso rolled to a 93-58 rout of Murray State in the Challenge in Music City on Saturday night. Valparaiso led 43-37 at the break and the Crusaders opened the second half with an 18-6 run, capped by Peters' six-straight points, to take a 61-44 lead with 14:00 to play. The Crusaders led by double digits the rest of the way. David Skara added 10 points for Valparaiso (6-1). Cameron Payne and T.J. Sapp hit back-to-back 3-pointers to pull Murray State within 39-37 with 1:28 remaining in the first half. Peters answered with four points to end the period. Jeffery Moss scored 13 points and Payne added 12 to lead Murray State (2-4). Valparaiso plays undefeated Portland, and Murray State faces Drake on Sunday.
